<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be a good hand • have good hands</xh5><p> <i>be a good hand—</i>1. be a diligent, industrious worker: He <u>is a good hand</u> and enjoys his work which he does faithfully and well. 2. possess the necessary skill to do smth. well: He <u>is a good hand</u> at making bows and arrows, and a fine knife would be just the thing for him.</p><p> <i>have good hands</i>—(Sport) have the ability to throw a ball well: Chris <u>has good hands</u>, catches the ball well in traffic and is quick enough.</p> </entry>
